WEBVTT

00:00:10.811 --> 00:00:12.946 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[music playing]

00:00:22.122 --> 00:00:25.058 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
It's such a blessing to have
a place like this to sit

00:00:25.058 --> 00:00:28.262 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
and just smell the air
and hear the creek.

00:00:32.499 --> 00:00:34.935 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
And know that I'll fade into
it at some point in my life.

00:00:40.741 --> 00:00:45.612 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:63%
I'm 53 years old and was
told about five weeks ago

00:00:45.612 --> 00:00:46.847 align:middle line:15% position:48% size:38%
that I'm dying.

00:00:49.750 --> 00:00:53.220 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
I've been given about six to
eight months left to live,

00:00:53.220 --> 00:00:55.355 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
and that's really what's
happening in my life

00:00:55.355 --> 00:00:57.524 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:35%
at the moment.

00:00:57.524 --> 00:01:00.427 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
Being OK with dying is
a weird place to be.

00:01:00.427 --> 00:01:02.930 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
It's very disconnected from
most of the people I know.

00:01:02.930 --> 00:01:04.531 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:45%
They don't get it.

00:01:04.531 --> 00:01:07.901 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
They think that I've given in.

00:01:07.901 --> 00:01:11.772 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
It's still really hard
for me to talk about it.

00:01:11.772 --> 00:01:19.913 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:58%
I know that he's upset
about dying and leaving

00:01:19.913 --> 00:01:21.815 align:middle line:15% position:48% size:38%
his loved ones.

00:01:21.815 --> 00:01:26.586 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
But what's amazing is that he's
so at peace with this journey

00:01:26.586 --> 00:01:29.256 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
that he's going
through and where it's

00:01:29.256 --> 00:01:31.858 align:middle line:85% position:45% size:73%
going to take him afterwards.

00:01:31.858 --> 00:01:36.029 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
What keeps me 
non-agitated about death

00:01:36.029 --> 00:01:38.966 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
is appreciation for the
life I've already had.

00:01:38.966 --> 00:01:41.435 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
I've had a beautiful
marriage, and my kids

00:01:41.435 --> 00:01:42.903 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:50%
are fabulous people.

00:01:42.903 --> 00:01:48.809 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:73%
And they hold, fortunately,
some of the best parts of me.

00:01:48.809 --> 00:01:51.345 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[music playing]

00:02:09.162 --> 00:02:11.465 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:50%
Have you had any
experiences yourself

00:02:11.465 --> 00:02:14.668 align:middle line:10% position:45% size:73%
that give you an insight into
what happens when we die?

00:02:14.668 --> 00:02:17.471 align:middle line:10% position:48% size:48%
I've thought about
death since the age

00:02:17.471 --> 00:02:23.010 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:81%
of six years when my grandfather
passed away suddenly.

00:02:23.010 --> 00:02:29.683 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
It's taken me almost a
lifetime to fully comprehend

00:02:29.683 --> 00:02:36.289 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
that death is an ongoing process
that makes life possible.

00:02:36.289 --> 00:02:41.094 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
What makes the universe
fresh is that it's dying

00:02:41.094 --> 00:02:43.497 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
and it's being reborn, and
it's dying, being reborn.

00:02:43.497 --> 00:02:46.633 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:48%
And every time it's
reborn, it actually

00:02:46.633 --> 00:02:48.835 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
creates a better
version of itself,

00:02:48.835 --> 00:02:51.271 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:63%
and we call it evolution.

00:02:53.974 --> 00:02:56.476 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:50%
In the United States
of America, I'd

00:02:56.476 --> 00:02:59.046 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:63%
say most people pretend
that death doesn't exist.

00:02:59.046 --> 00:03:02.883 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:53%
They call it a crime,
or call it a mistake,

00:03:02.883 --> 00:03:04.684 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:45%
they don't want
to do with it all.

00:03:04.684 --> 00:03:08.355 align:middle line:10% position:48% size:48%
And actually, death
is our birthright.

00:03:08.355 --> 00:03:11.124 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:43%
So to think of it
in any other way

00:03:11.124 --> 00:03:16.063 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:73%
is really just asking for
misery and pain in your life.

00:03:16.063 --> 00:03:17.664 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:58%
Because everybody dies.

00:03:17.664 --> 00:03:24.004 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
Every form of life dies--
what we call "dies."

00:03:24.004 --> 00:03:29.543 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
We came today because one of
the gibbons died recently,

00:03:29.543 --> 00:03:34.014 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
and Nikko, the partner, is
here and apparently he's

00:03:34.014 --> 00:03:35.682 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:43%
been in a kind of
state of grief.

00:03:35.682 --> 00:03:39.152 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:61%
Nikko had a mate that he
lived with, named Onyx,

00:03:39.152 --> 00:03:42.022 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:63%
and they've been together
since 1986, which

00:03:42.022 --> 00:03:44.291 align:middle line:15% position:50% size:75%
is a very long time, 26 years.

00:03:44.291 --> 00:03:46.026 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:48%
Gibbons in the wild
are monogamous,

00:03:46.026 --> 00:03:50.530 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
so it's pretty common for
them to have that pair bond.

00:03:50.530 --> 00:03:52.065 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:70%
They tend to stick together.

00:03:52.065 --> 00:03:54.267 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
They're one of the very few
primates that is monogamous.

00:03:54.267 --> 00:03:56.103 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:33%
Most are not.

00:03:56.103 --> 00:03:59.039 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:43%
Definitely that
was hard for him.

00:03:59.039 --> 00:04:03.043 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
His activity level decreased
pretty significantly.

00:04:03.043 --> 00:04:06.580 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
Gibbons in the wild will do this
beautiful song every morning,

00:04:06.580 --> 00:04:09.783 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
and it's a duet between
the bonded pair,

00:04:09.783 --> 00:04:12.586 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
and he stopped singing
for several weeks.

00:04:12.586 --> 00:04:15.222 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
We're at about eight
or nine weeks out now,

00:04:15.222 --> 00:04:18.291 align:start line:79% position:44% size:78%
and he's really starting to get
back to normal, which is great.

00:04:18.291 --> 00:04:20.393 align:middle line:85% position:44% size:78%
We're really happy to see that.

00:04:20.393 --> 00:04:24.064 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
We're sad when animals
die, but birth and death

00:04:24.064 --> 00:04:25.732 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
is all part of the same cycle.

00:04:25.732 --> 00:04:28.068 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
And you know, when leaves
fall and decompose,

00:04:28.068 --> 00:04:29.970 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:63%
it makes the soil richer.

00:04:29.970 --> 00:04:33.640 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:73%
So you really do have to have
all aspects of life and death

00:04:33.640 --> 00:04:37.010 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
to live on this beautiful
planet that we live on.

00:04:37.010 --> 00:04:38.578 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[music playing]

00:04:44.584 --> 00:04:47.254 align:middle line:10% position:45% size:73%
Deep within us, for reasons
that still strike me as quite

00:04:47.254 --> 00:04:49.122 align:middle line:10% position:48% size:48%
mysterious, I think
every organism

00:04:49.122 --> 00:04:53.660 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:81%
knows how to die, whether it's
a deer that finally just relaxes

00:04:53.660 --> 00:04:56.096 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:63%
in the mouth of the lion,
or thinking, myself,

00:04:56.096 --> 00:05:00.967 align:middle line:10% position:45% size:73%
about a rock climbing story--
a fellow on El Capitan,

00:05:00.967 --> 00:05:03.637 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:65%
3,000 feet high, rappelled
off the end of his rope.

00:05:06.606 --> 00:05:09.009 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
He forgot to tie a knot
in the end of his rope,

00:05:09.009 --> 00:05:12.012 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
so he just came off the end of
his rope and started falling.

00:05:12.012 --> 00:05:15.615 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
And people watching him told
me that he started screaming

00:05:15.615 --> 00:05:17.817 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
and writhing in the air,
trying to walk in the air,

00:05:17.817 --> 00:05:20.086 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:63%
which you just cannot do.

00:05:20.086 --> 00:05:23.490 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
And then after a few seconds
of that, just opened out.

00:05:23.490 --> 00:05:26.092 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
He relaxed and opened
out, as if he knew,

00:05:26.092 --> 00:05:28.361 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
you know, I don't want to spend
the last 10 seconds my life--

00:05:28.361 --> 00:05:30.130 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
because that's about how
long it takes to fall,

00:05:30.130 --> 00:05:32.566 align:start line:79% position:44% size:78%
roughly-- I don't want to spend
that panicking, and struggling,

00:05:32.566 --> 00:05:33.934 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:35%
and resisting.

00:05:33.934 --> 00:05:35.669 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
There's something in us
that knows how to open out.

00:05:35.669 --> 00:05:36.436 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[music playing]

00:05:38.438 --> 00:05:41.141 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
We've been doing
research on the idea

00:05:41.141 --> 00:05:43.143 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
that consciousness
may be something that

00:05:43.143 --> 00:05:46.146 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:70%
is more than just the brain.

00:05:46.146 --> 00:05:49.149 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
It may involve the brain, but
it may reach beyond the brain.

00:05:49.149 --> 00:05:51.651 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
For example, we've done
a series of experiments

00:05:51.651 --> 00:05:56.056 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
that look at the possibility
that one person's intention can

00:05:56.056 --> 00:05:59.659 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
influence another person's
biology, their physiology,

00:05:59.659 --> 00:06:02.495 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
at a distance and with
no sensory communication

00:06:02.495 --> 00:06:04.664 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:58%
between the two people.

00:06:04.664 --> 00:06:07.867 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
This speaks to the idea that
consciousness is more than just

00:06:07.867 --> 00:06:11.438 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
our physical being,
and that in fact, there

00:06:11.438 --> 00:06:13.873 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
may be ways in which
consciousness transcends

00:06:13.873 --> 00:06:15.308 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:31%
physicality.

00:06:15.308 --> 00:06:18.945 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
The implications of that
for what happens when we die

00:06:18.945 --> 00:06:21.114 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
is that perhaps there's
something more to our essence.

00:06:25.919 --> 00:06:29.422 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:63%
The event that changed my
life was, I was on my way

00:06:29.422 --> 00:06:31.491 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:53%
to dinner one
evening with my wife,

00:06:31.491 --> 00:06:33.560 align:middle line:10% position:48% size:43%
we'd been married
for five months.

00:06:33.560 --> 00:06:35.462 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
On our way to our
favorite restaurant,

00:06:35.462 --> 00:06:39.766 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
a van crossed the stop sign
at between 70 and 80 miles

00:06:39.766 --> 00:06:41.167 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:21%
an hour.

00:06:41.167 --> 00:06:47.073 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
It broadsided our
car and bulldozed us

00:06:47.073 --> 00:06:50.710 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
clear across 
Beverly Boulevard.

00:06:50.710 --> 00:06:53.246 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
The car took off and
flew through the air,

00:06:53.246 --> 00:06:56.216 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:48%
and hit that tree
in mid-air and came

00:06:56.216 --> 00:07:00.086 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
to rest in those
bushes over there.

00:07:00.086 --> 00:07:02.889 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
That night, the
doctor saved my life.

00:07:02.889 --> 00:07:04.324 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
I was at the deepest
level of coma

00:07:04.324 --> 00:07:08.361 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
that they measure, a
Glasgow Coma Scale 3.

00:07:08.361 --> 00:07:10.797 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
When I came out of the
coma, pieces of memory

00:07:10.797 --> 00:07:12.899 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:53%
started to come back.

00:07:12.899 --> 00:07:15.602 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
The memory from
my coma came to me

00:07:15.602 --> 00:07:18.138 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
of a protector who
was traveling with me

00:07:18.138 --> 00:07:20.206 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
through this inner space,
through this journey

00:07:20.206 --> 00:07:21.975 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:35%
into infinity.

00:07:25.245 --> 00:07:30.317 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
I was traveling through an
ancient grove on a boat,

00:07:30.317 --> 00:07:31.785 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
and I could hear
the sounds of rain

00:07:31.785 --> 00:07:34.154 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:70%
pattering down on the cabin.

00:07:34.154 --> 00:07:37.924 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
And there was a person
who was up one deck,

00:07:37.924 --> 00:07:40.226 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
who I knew I would be safe
if I could only just go up

00:07:40.226 --> 00:07:41.428 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
to be with her.

00:07:41.428 --> 00:07:43.263 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
And very slowly, in the
middle of the night,

00:07:43.263 --> 00:07:46.999 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
it occurred to me who
that protector was,

00:07:46.999 --> 00:07:49.269 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
and I realized it was my wife.

00:07:49.269 --> 00:07:53.940 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:73%
And the following morning, my
mother came to the hospital

00:07:53.940 --> 00:07:57.177 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
to explain that I hadn't
always been in this room,

00:07:57.177 --> 00:07:58.778 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:41%
and in this bed.

00:07:58.778 --> 00:08:00.814 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:61%
The reason I was in this
room, and in this bed,

00:08:00.814 --> 00:08:03.283 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:50%
was because I'd been
in an accident--

00:08:03.283 --> 00:08:06.786 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:75%
that before this room and this
bed, I'd been a filmmaker,

00:08:06.786 --> 00:08:09.255 align:middle line:10% position:48% size:48%
and that yes, I was
married to Marcy,

00:08:09.255 --> 00:08:11.791 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:58%
and that she died
instantly in the crash.

00:08:11.791 --> 00:08:15.061 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
And during my month in
coma, she had been laid

00:08:15.061 --> 00:08:17.831 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:70%
to rest in Phoenix, Arizona.

00:08:17.831 --> 00:08:22.969 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
So I'd lost everything, really,
that mattered most to me,

00:08:22.969 --> 00:08:25.105 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:73%
and that started this
journey through consciousness

00:08:25.105 --> 00:08:30.443 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
to find what makes us who we
are, could I recover who I was,

00:08:30.443 --> 00:08:32.879 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
and also to find a
reason to go forward.

00:08:32.879 --> 00:08:34.614 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[music playing]

00:08:41.087 --> 00:08:43.790 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:63%
Tony Redhouse is a Native
American practitioner

00:08:43.790 --> 00:08:46.192 align:middle line:15% position:50% size:65%
from the Navajo tradition.

00:08:46.192 --> 00:08:50.330 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
His work with hospice patients
and people in life transition

00:08:50.330 --> 00:08:52.365 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
connects him with the
importance of living

00:08:52.365 --> 00:08:54.868 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:65%
with the reality of death.

00:08:54.868 --> 00:08:58.238 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:45%
When you're laying
in a hospice bed,

00:08:58.238 --> 00:09:02.342 align:middle line:10% position:46% size:68%
you are going to look at
your whole life, everything

00:09:02.342 --> 00:09:09.349 align:start line:10% position:50% size:81%
that you've created, and whether
you have lived true to yourself

00:09:09.349 --> 00:09:12.919 align:middle line:10% position:44% size:78%
or whether you have lived your
whole life for the expectations

00:09:12.919 --> 00:09:14.521 align:middle line:15% position:50% size:45%
of everybody else.

00:09:14.521 --> 00:09:21.094 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
My idea of life and death
is focusing on the present.

00:09:21.094 --> 00:09:24.364 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
And what I've learned
in this is that if I

00:09:24.364 --> 00:09:29.436 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
think about what it is right now
that I really want to fulfill,

00:09:29.436 --> 00:09:33.239 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
what dream do I want to fulfill
in my life right now, that I

00:09:33.239 --> 00:09:36.376 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
have the ability, the
passion, to do these things,

00:09:36.376 --> 00:09:38.178 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:56%
the energy to do them.

00:09:38.178 --> 00:09:40.980 align:middle line:85% position:44% size:78%
I'm going to do them right now.

00:09:43.383 --> 00:09:45.718 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
I first got interested
in doing this work,

00:09:45.718 --> 00:09:48.121 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:43%
really when I was
a undergraduate.

00:09:48.121 --> 00:09:51.191 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:65%
And I was at a small, very
competitive university

00:09:51.191 --> 00:09:53.960 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:65%
that half the student body
graduated first or second

00:09:53.960 --> 00:09:55.662 align:middle line:15% position:45% size:73%
in their high school classes.

00:09:55.662 --> 00:09:57.397 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
It also turned out
to be the school that

00:09:57.397 --> 00:09:59.833 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
had the highest suicide rate in
the country per capita, which

00:09:59.833 --> 00:10:01.701 align:middle line:85% position:44% size:78%
wasn't in their course catalog.

00:10:01.701 --> 00:10:04.504 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
And the more I worried
about doing well,

00:10:04.504 --> 00:10:06.406 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
the harder it became to
study, and the harder

00:10:06.406 --> 00:10:09.275 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
it became to study, the
harder it became to do well.

00:10:09.275 --> 00:10:10.577 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
And I got into
this vicious cycle

00:10:10.577 --> 00:10:12.479 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
where I literally couldn't
sleep for a week straight.

00:10:15.148 --> 00:10:18.218 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
I remember sitting
in physics class,

00:10:18.218 --> 00:10:20.153 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
and I thought, you know,
I'll just kill myself.

00:10:20.153 --> 00:10:21.654 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
Why didn't I think
of that earlier?

00:10:21.654 --> 00:10:24.958 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:48%
That'll put and end
to all this pain.

00:10:24.958 --> 00:10:27.160 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
Because I came so close
to killing myself,

00:10:27.160 --> 00:10:28.461 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:50%
that was my doorway.

00:10:28.461 --> 00:10:30.430 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
You know, I came about as
close to doing that as you can

00:10:30.430 --> 00:10:32.165 align:middle line:85% position:45% size:73%
do without actually doing it.

00:10:32.165 --> 00:10:33.967 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
So naturally, I started
to ask questions.

00:10:33.967 --> 00:10:35.335 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:50%
What is death about?

00:10:35.335 --> 00:10:37.136 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
Is death, you know, just
you kind of close your eyes

00:10:37.136 --> 00:10:39.506 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
and go to sleep, or is it
something more than that?

00:10:42.976 --> 00:10:45.612 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
We know that people have
a lot of fear of death.

00:10:45.612 --> 00:10:48.448 align:middle line:10% position:48% size:48%
How do you see
this idea of death?

00:10:48.448 --> 00:10:54.621 align:middle line:10% position:44% size:78%
When the autumn comes, the
leaves are brown, and the fall.

00:10:54.621 --> 00:10:56.756 align:middle line:15% position:47% size:53%
And where do they go?

00:10:56.756 --> 00:10:58.958 align:middle line:15% position:46% size:68%
They go back into the soil.

00:10:58.958 --> 00:11:02.695 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
That nutrition of those leaves,
which becomes like compost,

00:11:02.695 --> 00:11:06.699 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
goes into the roots,
and they come back

00:11:06.699 --> 00:11:09.469 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
and the new leaves
are born again.

00:11:09.469 --> 00:11:12.539 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
So the old leaves, if
they were afraid of dying,

00:11:12.539 --> 00:11:14.607 align:middle line:85% position:45% size:73%
how the new leaves will come?

00:11:14.607 --> 00:11:17.477 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:43%
We are members of
the life force,

00:11:17.477 --> 00:11:19.479 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
and that life force continues.

00:11:19.479 --> 00:11:21.581 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:65%
It's a dynamic life force.

00:11:21.581 --> 00:11:25.485 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
If we become static in
one body and never die,

00:11:25.485 --> 00:11:27.420 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
and we are afraid
of dying, that means

00:11:27.420 --> 00:11:31.224 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
we are blocking the
dynamic force, which

00:11:31.224 --> 00:11:35.862 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
is ever changing, ever evolving,
ever transforming life force.

00:11:35.862 --> 00:11:38.831 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
If we block that, world
will be a boring place.

00:11:43.469 --> 00:11:44.837 align:middle line:15% position:48% size:38%
