Now start thinking of
people you love, those that

00:47:05.990 --> 00:47:06.791 align:middle line:85% position:46% size:68%
bring meaning to your life.

00:47:09.960 --> 00:47:15.366 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
Begin to feel the sense of
appreciation in your body.

00:47:15.366 --> 00:47:18.769 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:73%
Do you feel it in your chest,
your stomach, your back?

00:47:21.872 --> 00:47:25.376 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:48%
Continue to breathe
deeply in and out.

00:47:29.513 --> 00:47:32.717 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
Now think of a place
that you'd love to be,

00:47:32.717 --> 00:47:35.820 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
a place that brings you peace.

00:47:35.820 --> 00:47:38.656 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
And image yourself
in that place.

00:47:42.526 --> 00:47:44.462 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
And now you're joined
in that place by someone

00:47:44.462 --> 00:47:45.029 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:41%
you really love.

00:47:48.132 --> 00:47:50.034 align:middle line:85% position:46% size:68%
Allow them to sit with you.

00:47:53.971 --> 00:48:00.010 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:48%
Look at their face,
and in your mind,

00:48:00.010 --> 00:48:01.846 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:43%
tell them how you
feel about them.

00:48:09.120 --> 00:48:10.821 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
Returning to the place
we're born and raised

00:48:10.821 --> 00:48:13.691 align:middle line:85% position:44% size:78%
can be an emotional experience.

00:48:13.691 --> 00:48:19.063 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
It is for me, because of family
members who are now passed on.

00:48:19.063 --> 00:48:21.599 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:50%
I took my son
Skyler on pilgrimage

00:48:21.599 --> 00:48:23.768 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:53%
to pay final respects
to my mom and step

00:48:23.768 --> 00:48:27.938 align:middle line:15% position:44% size:78%
dad who died two years earlier.

00:48:27.938 --> 00:48:30.441 align:middle line:10% position:46% size:68%
My sisters arranged a
memorial service and burial

00:48:30.441 --> 00:48:32.710 align:middle line:10% position:48% size:43%
of their ashes in
the family plot,

00:48:32.710 --> 00:48:36.213 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:65%
a sweet good bye for
these two beautiful people

00:48:36.213 --> 00:48:38.582 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:70%
who played such an
important role in our lives.

00:48:43.721 --> 00:48:46.791 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
And I'm watching the
people that I love leave,

00:48:46.791 --> 00:48:51.262 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
and I am being left behind
by the people that I love.

00:48:51.262 --> 00:48:52.730 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
And then I have
to say the hardest

00:48:52.730 --> 00:48:55.733 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:63%
symptoms there is to say.

00:48:55.733 --> 00:48:59.003 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
I have to say
goodbye, I love you.

00:48:59.003 --> 00:49:02.439 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
How can it possibly be
goodbye, I love you,

00:49:02.439 --> 00:49:05.476 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:63%
in one sentence together?

00:49:05.476 --> 00:49:08.279 align:middle line:15% position:48% size:38%
[music playing]

00:49:27.832 --> 00:49:33.637 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:45%
This is my mother,
I lost her 2004.

00:49:33.637 --> 00:49:38.676 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
It's comforting to me that
I can come and talk to her,

00:49:38.676 --> 00:49:45.783 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
be with her, bring her flowers,
and just practice the way,

00:49:45.783 --> 00:49:47.017 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:70%
culturally, we do in Mexico.

00:49:50.354 --> 00:49:52.656 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
Clearly, the cross
cultural evidence

00:49:52.656 --> 00:49:54.258 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
suggests that people
all over the world,

00:49:54.258 --> 00:49:56.794 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
and throughout
history, have thought

00:49:56.794 --> 00:50:00.231 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:73%
that consciousness is more
than just our physical being.

00:50:00.231 --> 00:50:02.533 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
Different religions,
different cultural groups

00:50:02.533 --> 00:50:05.035 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
have created practices
to honor that transition.

00:50:17.281 --> 00:50:19.817 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
Many times when you
see your friends that

00:50:19.817 --> 00:50:22.887 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
do get hit, that are
sitting beside you--

00:50:22.887 --> 00:50:28.392 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
I've had several pilots come
out from under me-- and the fear

00:50:28.392 --> 00:50:31.896 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
hits afterward-- that's
when you feel it.

00:50:31.896 --> 00:50:37.501 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
I was down twice, and you
wonder why you make it and maybe

00:50:37.501 --> 00:50:38.836 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:43%
the pilot didn't.

00:50:38.836 --> 00:50:44.842 align:middle line:10% position:45% size:73%
I joined the service in 1966,
and I trained as a medic.

00:50:44.842 --> 00:50:48.078 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
And part of your training,
they teach you not

00:50:48.078 --> 00:50:50.581 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:70%
to care about your patients.

00:50:50.581 --> 00:50:54.585 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
It's a job, and that's all they
want to do is to do your job.

00:50:54.585 --> 00:50:58.522 align:middle line:10% position:45% size:73%
But what happens is that when
you have people, especially

00:50:58.522 --> 00:51:00.858 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:56%
the men who are coming
in off the field

00:51:00.858 --> 00:51:04.595 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:75%
and have been mortally wounded
and not expected to live,

00:51:04.595 --> 00:51:09.600 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:75%
your own personal feelings
start coming in and they-- you

00:51:09.600 --> 00:51:10.935 align:middle line:15% position:48% size:33%
start caring.

00:51:10.935 --> 00:51:13.137 align:middle line:15% position:50% size:75%
And there isn't any other way.

00:51:13.137 --> 00:51:17.041 align:middle line:10% position:48% size:43%
It's-- for me, it
was just really,

00:51:17.041 --> 00:51:19.877 align:middle line:10% position:45% size:73%
I just had to stop and just--
right now I'm having to do

00:51:19.877 --> 00:51:22.880 align:middle line:15% position:49% size:13%
this.

00:51:22.880 --> 00:51:24.882 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
Just really brings
a tear to your eyes.

00:51:24.882 --> 00:51:26.917 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
We honor the memory of
those who gave their lives

00:51:26.917 --> 00:51:29.420 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
in the service of our country.

00:51:29.420 --> 00:51:32.122 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
And of those others who
have dropped their burdens

00:51:32.122 --> 00:51:34.391 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:58%
by the wayside of life.

00:51:34.391 --> 00:51:35.626 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[music playing]

00:51:43.334 --> 00:51:47.838 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
When people use art at the end
of life, or people in grief,

00:51:47.838 --> 00:51:52.776 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
as a way of processing
their emotions.

00:51:52.776 --> 00:51:59.450 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
People have used art as a mode
of expressing emotions, grief.

00:51:59.450 --> 00:52:02.753 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
Art is a mode of inquiry
into consciousness.

00:52:02.753 --> 00:52:07.791 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:43%
Now, the moment
of death is known

00:52:07.791 --> 00:52:12.262 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
to have this experience
of life review.

00:52:12.262 --> 00:52:15.699 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
But then when you are
going through these,

00:52:15.699 --> 00:52:18.002 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
in the passage in
here, it says if you're

00:52:18.002 --> 00:52:21.672 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:48%
passing through all
your experiences

00:52:21.672 --> 00:52:23.173 align:middle line:85% position:46% size:68%
before you totally release.

00:52:27.845 --> 00:52:29.446 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
When I first saw
footage of elephants

00:52:29.446 --> 00:52:31.982 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
encountering the remains
of another elephant,

00:52:31.982 --> 00:52:34.018 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:48%
I was deeply moved.

00:52:34.018 --> 00:52:36.854 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
You could see that they were
very interested, certainly

00:52:36.854 --> 00:52:37.988 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:21%
curious.

00:52:37.988 --> 00:52:39.923 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:50%
Where they grieving?

00:52:39.923 --> 00:52:41.959 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
Each member of the herd
explored the remains

00:52:41.959 --> 00:52:44.428 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:48%
using their sense
of smell and touch,

00:52:44.428 --> 00:52:47.464 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
as if looking for clues
about what happened,

00:52:47.464 --> 00:52:49.433 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
or in remembrance of
events in the life

00:52:49.433 --> 00:52:51.969 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:70%
of their departed companion.

00:52:51.969 --> 00:52:56.040 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
You know, grieving is an
important part of the process,

00:52:56.040 --> 00:52:58.442 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:48%
and it's necessary.

00:52:58.442 --> 00:53:00.544 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:73%
That's how we look at it with
the zoo-- an animal dies,

00:53:00.544 --> 00:53:02.379 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:48%
but there are still
other animals that

00:53:02.379 --> 00:53:05.783 align:start line:79% position:44% size:78%
are counting on us, and we need
to continue to do our best take

00:53:05.783 --> 00:53:08.786 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:56%
care of those animals.

00:53:08.786 --> 00:53:13.157 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
So if you have members of your
congregation that are in grief,

00:53:13.157 --> 00:53:14.858 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
what do you do?

00:53:14.858 --> 00:53:20.230 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:70%
If I really want to quiet
and be present with my heart

00:53:20.230 --> 00:53:23.700 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:53%
and the grief in it,
I walk the labyrinth.

00:53:23.700 --> 00:53:27.137 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
The labyrinth is a
pattern, actually.

00:53:27.137 --> 00:53:30.007 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
It's usually about
a 40 foot circle,

00:53:30.007 --> 00:53:34.011 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
and it has one path that starts
at the outer edge, and weaves

00:53:34.011 --> 00:53:38.048 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
in a very circuitous way,
eventually into center.

00:53:38.048 --> 00:53:40.350 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
And what it is is a
walking meditation where

00:53:40.350 --> 00:53:45.022 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
you find your natural pace,
and that's pretty rare.

00:53:45.022 --> 00:53:47.091 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
By walking, the mind
quiets much easier.

00:53:52.563 --> 00:53:57.367 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
I know we are here to
celebrate David's live,

00:53:57.367 --> 00:54:00.704 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
but I would not be
honest if I didn't

00:54:00.704 --> 00:54:12.049 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
say that I'm grieving right
now, and my heart is broken.

00:54:12.049 --> 00:54:16.053 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
I grieved over David
as a brother would.

00:54:16.053 --> 00:54:20.357 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
Grief is something that
you must go through.

00:54:20.357 --> 00:54:26.396 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
You must feel it, embody
it, experience it,

00:54:26.396 --> 00:54:28.132 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:61%
and it has a life cycle.

00:54:28.132 --> 00:54:32.069 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
It, you know, it reaches a peak,
and then it rains, and then

00:54:32.069 --> 00:54:35.239 align:middle line:85% position:44% size:78%
slowly dissipates as an energy.

00:54:35.239 --> 00:54:43.080 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
And when it dissipates, then
you revive the bond, the love,

00:54:43.080 --> 00:54:45.082 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:56%
that was always there.

00:54:45.082 --> 00:54:48.619 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
OK, and then you have a
relationship with that person.

00:54:48.619 --> 00:54:52.422 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
And that person doesn't have to
be perceptually right in front

00:54:52.422 --> 00:54:54.625 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
of you, they're in
your consciousness

00:54:54.625 --> 00:54:56.160 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
and you have access to
them anytime you want.

00:55:01.064 --> 00:55:03.901 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
I think that everyone has their
own way of getting through it,

00:55:03.901 --> 00:55:08.138 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
but once you have an awareness
that life is eternal,

00:55:08.138 --> 00:55:13.110 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
you miss the person-- I
miss my mom, you miss them--

00:55:13.110 --> 00:55:14.845 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
but you have a
different relationship,

00:55:14.845 --> 00:55:16.446 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:53%
because they're here.

00:55:16.446 --> 00:55:19.816 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:48%
You know, they're
around, and it just

00:55:19.816 --> 00:55:21.084 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:48%
becomes a different
relationship.

00:55:21.084 --> 00:55:22.853 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[music playing]

00:55:29.126 --> 00:55:30.827 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:50%
In the Christian
tradition, you know,

00:55:30.827 --> 00:55:34.498 align:middle line:10% position:44% size:78%
we've had many versions over
the century of death and dying,

00:55:34.498 --> 00:55:37.100 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:53%
but I think certainly
the major tenant

00:55:37.100 --> 00:55:40.804 align:middle line:10% position:44% size:78%
is that there's a life beyond,
after the body, or after death.

00:55:40.804 --> 00:55:43.407 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
I do really truly
understand that there's

00:55:43.407 --> 00:55:45.209 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
consciousness beyond
death, there's

00:55:45.209 --> 00:55:47.678 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
consciousness beyond the body.

00:55:47.678 --> 00:55:50.681 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
And I think that's
what we mean by soul.

00:55:50.681 --> 00:55:53.884 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
The soul really can
awaken, we know that.

00:55:53.884 --> 00:55:56.520 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:43%
It's often asleep
for many people.

00:55:56.520 --> 00:56:01.024 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
And as we become more conscious
of this part of ourselves,

00:56:01.024 --> 00:56:04.895 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
we really, I think, want to
guard that, protect that,

00:56:04.895 --> 00:56:07.264 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
grow that, be in love with it.

00:56:12.402 --> 00:56:15.672 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:58%
This is a good subject,
because it's universal.

00:56:15.672 --> 00:56:17.874 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:58%
Whether you're
Christian, or Buddhist,

00:56:17.874 --> 00:56:21.511 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:75%
or Muslim, or Atheist,
everybody meets in that point,

00:56:21.511 --> 00:56:24.348 align:middle line:15% position:48% size:43%
we call it death.

00:56:24.348 --> 00:56:27.918 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
It says in the Surah that
Prophet, peace be upon him,

00:56:27.918 --> 00:56:32.222 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
was teaching, he
said, "Blessed the one

00:56:32.222 --> 00:56:35.859 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:70%
who created death and life."

00:56:35.859 --> 00:56:39.663 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
Usually, you think life and
death, we call this life,

00:56:39.663 --> 00:56:42.199 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
and we call, that the
end, you know, this.

00:56:42.199 --> 00:56:46.203 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:73%
But in that teaching, he
calls this whole life, death,

00:56:46.203 --> 00:56:49.239 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
and he calls the
after death, life.

00:56:49.239 --> 00:56:50.774 align:middle line:85% position:45% size:73%
Because this one has a limit.

00:56:50.774 --> 00:56:54.211 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:48%
You're born and
you have an ending.

00:56:54.211 --> 00:56:55.912 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
The other one doesn't
have an ending.

00:56:55.912 --> 00:56:56.680 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
[music playing]

00:56:59.883 --> 00:57:02.586 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:61%
I think one of the
great advantages of most

00:57:02.586 --> 00:57:05.222 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:53%
traditional religions
is that they make

00:57:05.222 --> 00:57:07.724 align:middle line:15% position:50% size:70%
people less afraid of death.

00:57:07.724 --> 00:57:11.094 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
I mean, death's scary,
especially if it's painful.

00:57:11.094 --> 00:57:12.996 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
But they make people
less afraid of death,

00:57:12.996 --> 00:57:16.233 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
because this is the feeling
that death is a transition.

00:57:16.233 --> 00:57:18.035 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
If you're a materialist
or an atheist,

00:57:18.035 --> 00:57:20.103 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
and you believe that
death is the end

00:57:20.103 --> 00:57:23.340 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:73%
and the mind just goes blank,
you may be scared of that,

00:57:23.340 --> 00:57:25.575 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:63%
or scared of growing old.

00:57:25.575 --> 00:57:28.912 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
I think that the main
purpose of religion

00:57:28.912 --> 00:57:31.548 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
is to make people feel
that their lives are

00:57:31.548 --> 00:57:33.250 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:58%
part of something
bigger than themselves,

00:57:33.250 --> 00:57:36.053 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
that they're connected
to something much larger

00:57:36.053 --> 00:57:36.953 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:41%
than themselves.

00:57:36.953 --> 00:57:38.755 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:43%
And that includes
something larger

00:57:38.755 --> 00:57:42.259 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
than themselves in
relation to death.

00:57:42.259 --> 00:57:44.594 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:43%
If people choose
a spiritual path,

00:57:44.594 --> 00:57:47.164 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
you know, whatever
path that is for them,

00:57:47.164 --> 00:57:49.833 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
and only they know what's right
for them, and stick with it,

00:57:49.833 --> 00:57:54.271 align:start line:79% position:50% size:81%
you get these direct experiences
of, on one level, I'm separate,

00:57:54.271 --> 00:57:56.606 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
you're you, and I'm me, and
another, I'm part of something

00:57:56.606 --> 00:57:58.775 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:70%
larger that connects us all.

00:58:01.978 --> 00:58:03.980 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:50%
I think that the
universe is becoming

00:58:03.980 --> 00:58:07.451 align:middle line:10% position:47% size:63%
self conscious through
the human nervous system.

00:58:07.451 --> 00:58:12.989 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
The [inaudible] that knows is
is an omnipresent, omniscient,

00:58:12.989 --> 00:58:16.593 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
omnipotent being--
the cosmic mind.

00:58:16.593 --> 00:58:19.663 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
And our mind is an
aspect of that mind.

00:58:19.663 --> 00:58:22.299 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
As the great poet Rumi
says, "You're not just

00:58:22.299 --> 00:58:27.738 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
a drop in the ocean, you're
the mighty ocean in the drop."

00:58:27.738 --> 00:58:30.540 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:43%
The Indian sages
had this allegory

00:58:30.540 --> 00:58:34.177 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
of pots of water
put in the sunlight.

00:58:34.177 --> 00:58:37.314 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
You take a million pots
and fill them with water,

00:58:37.314 --> 00:58:40.183 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
and the sun is shining, the
sun is in each one of them,

00:58:40.183 --> 00:58:42.686 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
but there's only one sentence.

00:58:42.686 --> 00:58:44.888 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
So, you know, you
take a million people,

00:58:44.888 --> 00:58:47.391 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
that all our conscious is
only one consciousness.

00:58:51.328 --> 00:58:52.996 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:43%
What I know for
sure about death,

00:58:52.996 --> 00:58:59.302 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
it's just a passageway, a
doorway into ever unfolding

00:58:59.302 --> 00:59:01.405 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
of who and what we really are.

00:59:01.405 --> 00:59:03.707 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:41%
And it's nothing
to be afraid of.

00:59:03.707 --> 00:59:06.610 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
When the time comes,
it's a common denominator

00:59:06.610 --> 00:59:08.578 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:63%
that we all pass through.

00:59:08.578 --> 00:59:11.348 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
Know that one day, we're
not going to have this body,

00:59:11.348 --> 00:59:15.051 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
so while we're here, in a
human incarnation, we can ask,

00:59:15.051 --> 00:59:16.486 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:41%
how can I serve?

00:59:16.486 --> 00:59:18.054 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
How can I love?

00:59:18.054 --> 00:59:21.091 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
How can I cultivate the
gifts that are within me,

00:59:21.091 --> 00:59:22.592 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:43%
and express them?

00:59:22.592 --> 00:59:26.830 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
Let me not leave without saying,
and being, and giving all

00:59:26.830 --> 00:59:30.901 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
that I can say, and be,
and give, while I'm here.

00:59:30.901 --> 00:59:33.804 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
I know unequivocally,
without any question,

00:59:33.804 --> 00:59:36.440 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:81%
there is no such thing as death.

00:59:36.440 --> 00:59:40.710 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
No one ever dies, you just
shift from one frequency

00:59:40.710 --> 00:59:43.113 align:middle line:85% position:47% size:58%
into another frequency.

00:59:43.113 --> 00:59:45.916 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
And more importantly, you go
back to where you originally

00:59:45.916 --> 00:59:46.283 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:25%
came from.

00:59:49.386 --> 00:59:52.389 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:81%
So scientifically, we don't
know if identity, self-awareness

00:59:52.389 --> 00:59:54.558 align:middle line:15% position:50% size:45%
can survive death.

00:59:54.558 --> 00:59:57.127 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:41%
That's more of a
spiritual belief

00:59:57.127 --> 00:59:59.396 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:45%
right now than a
scientific belief.

00:59:59.396 --> 01:00:02.065 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:61%
But I trust my intuition
more than anything,

01:00:02.065 --> 01:00:04.067 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:65%
and my intuition says yes,
this is probably the case.

01:00:07.404 --> 01:00:11.942 align:middle line:10% position:50% size:50%
Be aware that we are
part of a continuum.

01:00:11.942 --> 01:00:15.946 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:53%
We were here at the
time of the Big Bang.

01:00:15.946 --> 01:00:20.150 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
I never died, from the time
of Big Bang, I was here.

01:00:20.150 --> 01:00:24.154 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
And I will never die, I'll
be here for the eternity.

01:00:24.154 --> 01:00:27.190 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:48%
I only change form.

01:00:27.190 --> 01:00:31.962 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
The moment you realize
that, then you not afraid.

01:00:31.962 --> 01:00:36.199 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:56%
The dead are not under
the earth, you know?

01:00:36.199 --> 01:00:41.137 align:start line:79% position:50% size:81%
They're in the water, they're in
the woods, they're in the fire,

01:00:41.137 --> 01:00:44.007 align:middle line:79% position:46% size:68%
they're in the air, they're
in the breast of the woman,

01:00:44.007 --> 01:00:46.142 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
they're in the child
that is crying.

01:00:46.142 --> 01:00:48.545 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:56%
The dead are not dead.

01:00:48.545 --> 01:00:54.451 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
The key to the conquest of death
is to find out who you are.

01:00:54.451 --> 01:00:56.887 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:70%
As long as you confused with
your body and your mind,

01:00:56.887 --> 01:01:00.957 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
you're bamboozled
by superstition, OK?

01:01:00.957 --> 01:01:03.159 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
Because the body and the
mind are dying anyway,

01:01:03.159 --> 01:01:05.362 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:43%
all the time, OK?

01:01:05.362 --> 01:01:08.398 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
I don't have the same thoughts
I had when I was a teenager.

01:01:08.398 --> 01:01:10.467 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:43%
I don't have the
same personality.

01:01:10.467 --> 01:01:13.169 align:middle line:85% position:44% size:78%
I don't have the same emotions.

01:01:13.169 --> 01:01:15.272 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
If you're the string
of beads, there's

01:01:15.272 --> 01:01:18.808 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:73%
a thread that strings
together the string of beads.

01:01:18.808 --> 01:01:22.379 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
So when you think of the beads
as the memories and the string

01:01:22.379 --> 01:01:26.983 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
as what the memories
are strung on,

01:01:26.983 --> 01:01:32.489 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
that's you-- the string on which
the memories are strung on.

01:01:32.489 --> 01:01:34.491 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:48%
And if you can go
to the deeper level

01:01:34.491 --> 01:01:38.028 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
and be grounded there now,
you've conquered death.

01:01:38.028 --> 01:01:42.232 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
Because you realize that
death is an illusion.

01:01:42.232 --> 01:01:47.837 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
It's actually the movement
of space time events.

01:01:50.874 --> 01:01:54.644 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:48%
In coma, it's a
different universe.

01:01:54.644 --> 01:01:59.082 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
I had no sense of
concern, no anxiety.

01:01:59.082 --> 01:02:02.519 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:75%
I just found myself exploring.

01:02:02.519 --> 01:02:05.488 align:middle line:79% position:48% size:48%
It was an area of
complete curiosity.

01:02:05.488 --> 01:02:07.524 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:43%
It was boundless.

01:02:07.524 --> 01:02:11.194 align:middle line:85% position:50% size:81%
Vista, after vista, after vista.

01:02:11.194 --> 01:02:15.532 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
Every environment was
beautiful, one environment

01:02:15.532 --> 01:02:16.866 align:middle line:85% position:44% size:78%
leading seamlessly to the next.

01:02:20.637 --> 01:02:23.440 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:45%
The landscapes and
places I visited,

01:02:23.440 --> 01:02:26.543 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
I knew them well, although I
had never been to them before.

01:02:26.543 --> 01:02:30.113 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
The people I met, I felt
I'd known them for as long

01:02:30.113 --> 01:02:34.250 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:73%
as I could remember, although
I'd not met them before,

01:02:34.250 --> 01:02:37.554 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:81%
which is why I feel that we have
one consciousness that we all

01:02:37.554 --> 01:02:41.224 align:middle line:79% position:45% size:73%
share, in complete connection
with everything and everyone.

01:02:41.224 --> 01:02:44.494 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:38%
Very beautiful.

01:02:44.494 --> 01:02:48.598 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:65%
And whether we recover,
whether we wake up or not,

01:02:48.598 --> 01:02:53.803 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
there's no cause for fear
when we change-- when we

01:02:53.803 --> 01:02:55.805 align:middle line:85% position:44% size:78%
move into some other existence.

01:03:00.076 --> 01:03:04.914 align:middle line:10% position:45% size:73%
On the day when death will
knock at your door, what will

01:03:04.914 --> 01:03:07.283 align:middle line:15% position:50% size:41%
you give to him?

01:03:07.283 --> 01:03:11.921 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:75%
Oh, I will set before my guest
the full vessel of my life.

01:03:11.921 --> 01:03:15.025 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:50%
I will never let him
go with empty hands.

01:03:15.025 --> 01:03:21.598 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
All the sweet vintage of all my
autumn days and summer nights.

01:03:21.598 --> 01:03:25.502 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
All the earnings and
gleanings of my busy life

01:03:25.502 --> 01:03:29.506 align:middle line:79% position:50% size:61%
will I place before Him
at the close of my days.

01:03:29.506 --> 01:03:33.777 align:middle line:79% position:44% size:78%
Now the day has dawned, and the
lamp that lit my dark corner

01:03:33.777 --> 01:03:37.280 align:middle line:85% position:48% size:18%
is out.

01:03:37.280 --> 01:03:40.350 align:middle line:79% position:47% size:63%
A summons has come, and
I'm ready for my journey.

